description: California’s elected Democrats had tough words for President Donald Trump and the GOP Congress on Saturday, urging their party’s fired-up activists to work against the 14 Republicans in the state’s congressional delegation.
title: California Democrats take aim at Trump, GOP Congress

author: John Myers
description: The new leader of the California Democratic Party inherits a enormous legacy of campaign cash. The state party has spent $298 million since the year 2000.
title: Political Road Map: Democrats not only dominate California elections, the party is king of campaign cash

description: Indian-Americans have expressed anguish over the negative portrayal of Hinduism and India in the proposed California school textbooks. For the past several years, the Indian-American community has been battling to remove several inaccuracies and myths about Hinduism from the textbooks.
title: Indian-Americans unhappy with California school textbooks over portrayal of Hinduism - Times of India

description: Democratic delegates to the California Democratic Party convention in Sacramento on Saturday, May 20, 2017, think President Donald Trump should be impeached. Most in the state’s Democratic leadership were mum or opposed, concerned such appeals could trivialize an anti-Trump message in next year’s election.
title: California Democratic activists want Trump’s head, but leaders bat down impeachment calls

description: Coverage | Google I/O 2017 - Mountain View, California - May 17 - 19, 2017
title: Coverage

author: NICK PERRY
description: WELLINGTON, New Zealand (AP) — New Zealand has never had a space program but could soon be launching commercial rockets more often than the United States. That's if the plans of California-based company Rocket Lab work out. Founded by New Zealander Peter Beck, the company was last week given official approval to conduct three test launches from a remote peninsula in the South Pacific nation. Rocket Lab is planning the first launch of its Electron rocket sometime from Monday, depending on conditions.
title: New Zealand space launch has nation reaching for the stars
